{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a038", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 59, "line_end": 59, "verbatim": "This CRF collects details about injection site rash events at each visit, until resolved.", "parent_section": "§FA.2 [Example 2]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a039", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 61, "line_end": 61, "verbatim": "In this scenario, the injection site rash event was considered a reportable adverse event; therefore, the rash itself was represented in the AE domain. The rash assessment form collects a reference number for the AE, represented in AESPID. Certain required or expected variables have been omitted from the example dataset in consideration of space and clarity.", "parent_section": "§FA.2 [Example 2]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a040", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 63, "line_end": 63, "verbatim": "Additional data about the rash were collected at visits 3 and 4, which occurred 2 days and 9 days after the start of the rash. These data were represented in an FA dataset because they were not about the event as a whole (see Section 6.4.1, When to Use Findings About Events or Interventions, criterion 1). In addition, the measurement of the rash requires multiple variables (value and unit) for its representation and the numbers of various kinds of lesions within the rash are a set of similar assessments of the event (see Section 6.4.1, When to Use Findings About Events or Interventions, criterion 2).", "parent_section": "§FA.2 [Example 2]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Section 6.4.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a041", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 65, "line_end": 65, "verbatim": "**ae.xpt**", "parent_section": "§FA.2 [Example 2]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
