{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a065", "atom_type": "HEADING", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 99, "line_end": 99, "verbatim": "## Example 3", "parent_section": "§FA [FA — Examples]", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a066", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 101, "line_end": 101, "verbatim": "This CRF collects information about rheumatoid arthritis. In this scenario, rheumatoid arthritis is a prerequisite for participation in an osteoporosis trial and was not collected as a Medical History (MH) event.", "parent_section": "§FA.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a067", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 103, "line_end": 103, "verbatim": "In this study, data were collected only at baseline. Because the occurrence and severity apply to the symptoms as a whole, they are represented in the MH domain. Note that the average duration of early morning stiffness cannot be represented in MHDUR because MHDUR would be the duration of the entire event, rather than the average of daily durations.", "parent_section": "§FA.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a068", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 105, "line_end": 105, "verbatim": "**Row 1:** Because the CRF specifically collected date of diagnosis for rheumatoid arthritis, MHEVDTYP is populated with DIAGNOSIS to indicate that the date in MHSTDTC is the date of diagnosis.", "parent_section": "§FA.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a069", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 106, "line_end": 106, "verbatim": "**Rows 2-6:** No start or end dates were collected for the symptoms, so the variable MHEVDTYP is not relevant for those records. MHEVDTYP is used only to specify the aspect of the event used to determine start and/or end dates.", "parent_section": "§FA.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
