{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a132", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 199, "line_end": 199, "verbatim": "In this example, the sponsor's definition of \"event\" meant that 1 record would be created for each adverse event, covering it from start to finish (see Section 6.2.1, Adverse Events, assumption 6.4). The AE module also collected information about severity at each visit.", "parent_section": "§FA.6 [Example 6]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Section 6.2.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a133", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 201, "line_end": 201, "verbatim": "An electronic data collection instrument would probably be constructed as 2 related modules:", "parent_section": "§FA.6 [Example 6]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmFA_ex_a134", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FA/examples.md", "line_start": 202, "line_end": 202, "verbatim": "- A module for the adverse event, where a record would be entered for each event", "parent_section": "§FA.6 [Example 6]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T08:00:00Z"}}
